        "notes": [
            {
                "category": "summary",
                "text": "NVIDIA has released a software update for NVIDIA\u00ae DOCA Host and Mellanox OFED.<div>To protect your system, download and install the latest update from the <a href=\"https://developer.nvidia.com/doca-downloads\">DOCA Framework page</a>.  For earlier evaluation versions, contact your account manager to get access through NVOnline.</div>",
                "title": "Summary"
            },
            {
                "category": "legal_disclaimer",
                "text": "This content is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/). If you distribute this content, or a modified version of it, you must provide attribution to Red Hat Inc. and provide a link to the original.",
                "title": "Terms of Use"
            },
            {
                "category": "details",
                "text": "To protect your system, download and install the latest update from the <a href=\"https://developer.nvidia.com/doca-downloads\">DOCA Framework page</a>. For earlier evaluation versions, contact your account manager to get access through NVOnline.",
                "title": "Security Update Notes"
            },
            {
                "category": "details",
                "text": "VGT+ is a feature only for Mellanox OFED and DOCA-Host, and does not exist in upstream Linux, or INBOX. The VGT+ feature is not enabled by default. The vulnerability affects only systems with the VGT+ feature enabled and eSwitch in Legacy mode, where Legacy is the default. The scope of impact is limited to the VGT+ feature itself.<br><div>Upstream Linux VGT features can achieve similar separation between VLANs.<br></div><div>Review your network configurations and ensure that the VGT+ feature is not enabled unless necessary.<br></div><div>To determine if VGT+ is enabled for a specific SR-IOV (0 in this example), determine whether  the /sys/class/net/eth5/device/sriov/0/trunkfile exists and contains any values. If this file is missing or empty, VGT+ is not enabled.<br></div><div>To search for relevant files:<br></div><div>$&gt; sudo find /sys/class/net/ -name trunk\t<br></div><div>To check if the device is in Legacy mode:<br></div><div>$&gt; sudo find /sys/class/net -name mode -exec cat {} ;</div>",
                "title": "Mitigation Notes"
            },
            {
                "category": "details",
                "text": "<br>",
                "title": "Bulletin Notes"
            },
